---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import {
  NEUROWALL_VERSION,
  NEUROWALL_STATUS,
  NEUROWALL_LAYERS,
  NEUROWALL_DETECTION_RESULTS,
  NEUROWALL_STATS,
  NEUROWALL_POLICY_RULES,
  NEUROWALL_SPECS,
  NEUROWALL_DURATION_SWEEP,
  NEUROWALL_SOVEREIGNTY_ATTACKS,
} from '../lib/neurowall-constants';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Tools"
  description="QIF security tools: Neurowall hardware firewall, NSP post-quantum protocol, and Runemate on-device compiler. The defense stack for brain-computer interfaces."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Tools' }]}
  maxWidth="wide"
>
  <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-[240px_1fr] lg:gap-12">
    <!-- Sidebar (sticky TOC) -->
    <aside class="hidden lg:block">
      <nav class="sticky top-24 space-y-1" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wider uppercase text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-3">On this page</p>
        {[
          { href: '#overview', label: 'Overview' },
          { href: '#defense-stack', label: 'Defense Stack' },
          { href: '#neurowall', label: 'Neurowall' },
          { href: '#detection', label: 'Detection Results' },
          { href: '#sovereignty', label: 'Sovereignty Attacks' },
          { href: '#policy-engine', label: 'Policy Engine' },
          { href: '#tara-neurowall', label: 'TARA-Neurowall' },
          { href: '#nsp', label: 'NSP Protocol' },
          { href: '#runemate', label: 'Runemate' },
          { href: '#specs', label: 'Technical Specs' },
          { href: '#source', label: 'Source & Docs' },
        ].map((item) => (
          <a href={item.href} class="block text-sm py-1.5 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] transition-colors border-l-2 border-transparent hover:border-[var(--color-accent-primary)] pl-3">
            {item.label}
          </a>
        ))}
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <!-- Main content -->
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <!-- Overview -->
      <section id="overview" class="mb-20">
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-4">
          QIF Security Tools
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-6">
          QIF defines the threat model. These tools implement the defense. Three components form a vertically integrated security stack: a hardware firewall that guards inbound neural signals, a post-quantum wire protocol that secures data in transit, and an on-device compiler that enforces policy through safe bytecode execution.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
          Each tool is independently useful, but they were designed to work together. Neurowall detects and filters attacks at the signal boundary. NSP encrypts and authenticates every frame that passes through. Runemate compiles policy rules into on-chip bytecode that Neurowall's L3 policy agent executes, and delivers secure UI content over NSP sessions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Defense Stack -->
      <section id="defense-stack" class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-6">The Defense Stack</h2>
        <div class="prose mb-8">
          <p>
            The QIF defense stack positions Neurowall and Runemate as sibling components at the I0 (Neural Interface) bottleneck of the hourglass model. Neurowall guards the inbound signal path. Runemate guards the outbound rendering path. Both rest on NSP for cryptographic transport.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Neurowall -->
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-20 text-center">
                <span class="text-xs font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] px-2 py-1 rounded bg-[var(--color-accent-primary)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">Inbound</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Neurowall</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Hardware firewall for neural signals. Three concentric defense layers filter signal injection, protect against neural fingerprinting, and enforce security policy in real time. Guards the read path: raw EEG/EMG from electrodes through filtering, anomaly detection, and policy enforcement.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-2 border-dashed border-[var(--color-border)] ml-10 h-4"></div>

            <!-- NSP -->
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-20 text-center">
                <span class="text-xs font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] px-2 py-1 rounded bg-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]">Transport</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">NSP Protocol</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Post-quantum wire protocol. Handles key exchange (ML-KEM-768), frame encryption (AES-256-GCM-SIV), signature amortization (Merkle trees + ML-DSA), and 20-year key lifecycle management. Every neural data frame passes through NSP before leaving the device.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-2 border-dashed border-[var(--color-border)] ml-10 h-4"></div>

            <!-- Runemate -->
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <div class="shrink-0 w-20 text-center">
                <span class="text-xs font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] px-2 py-1 rounded bg-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)]">Outbound</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Runemate</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">On-device DSL compiler and execution engine. Compiles neural UI definitions and security policies into compact Staves bytecode. The Scribe interpreter runs on-chip in &lt; 200KB, executing policy rules for Neurowall's L3 agent and rendering safe multimodal content. Guards the write path.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Neurowall -->
      <section id="neurowall" class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-4">
          Neurowall <span class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">v{NEUROWALL_VERSION}</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <span class="text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]">
            {NEUROWALL_STATUS}
          </span>
        </div>
        <div class="prose mb-8">
          <p>
            Neurowall is a hardware-level security architecture for non-intrusive BCI wearables: smart glasses with temporal dry EEG/EOG sensors and subvocal collars with jawline EMG arrays. It provides three concentric defense layers that operate entirely on-device, with no dependency on a phone app or cloud service to enforce neural privacy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 3-Layer Defense -->
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {NEUROWALL_LAYERS.map((layer) => (
            <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6" style={`border-left: 3px solid ${layer.color};`}>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                <span class="text-sm font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)]" style={`color: ${layer.color};`}>L{layer.id}</span>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)]">{layer.name}</h3>
                <span class="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-text-faint)] ml-auto whitespace-nowrap">
                  {layer.type}
                </span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">{layer.description}</p>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                {layer.defenses.map((defense) => (
                  <span class="text-xs font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] px-2 py-0.5 rounded border border-[var(--color-border)] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
                    {defense}
                  </span>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <!-- How Neurowall uses NSP + Runemate -->
        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 mt-6" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent-secondary);">
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Integration:</strong> Neurowall does not build its own crypto or compression stack. L1 and L2 process raw signals on-device. All outbound data passes through <a href="/nsp/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] hover:underline">NSP</a> for post-quantum encryption and Merkle-authenticated transport. L3 policy rules are compiled by <a href="/runemate/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] hover:underline">Runemate's Forge</a>, signed with ML-DSA, and executed on-chip by the Scribe interpreter.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Detection Results -->
      <section id="detection" class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-6">Detection Results</h2>
        <div class="prose mb-8">
          <p>
            Neurowall's detection pipeline has been tested against 15 TARA-mapped attack scenarios, including 5 adversarial-aware attacks designed by attackers who understand the defense architecture. Results from simulation (v0.7) with single-run 15-second observation windows.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Stats row -->
        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-8 mb-8">
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-4 gap-8 text-center">
            <div>
              <p class="text-3xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">{NEUROWALL_STATS.detectedCount}/{NEUROWALL_STATS.totalAttacks}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1 uppercase tracking-wider">Attacks Detected</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-3xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]">{NEUROWALL_STATS.adversarialDetected}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1 uppercase tracking-wider">Adversarial-Aware</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-3xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-status-safe)]">{NEUROWALL_STATS.brainflow.fpr}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1 uppercase tracking-wider">False Positive Rate</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-3xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)]">{NEUROWALL_STATS.rocOptimal.duration_s}s</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1 uppercase tracking-wider">100% Detection</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Detection table -->
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium w-8">#</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Attack</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Detected By</th>
                <th class="text-right py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Result</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {NEUROWALL_DETECTION_RESULTS.filter(r => r.id > 0).map((row) => (
                <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/50">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">{row.id}</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium">{row.attack}</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{row.detectedBy}</td>
                  <td class={`py-3 px-4 text-right font-semibold text-xs uppercase tracking-wider ${row.result === 'detected' ? 'text-[var(--color-status-safe)]' : 'text-[var(--color-status-danger)]'}`}>
                    {row.result}
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- Duration sweep -->
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-4">Duration Sweep</h3>
        <div class="prose mb-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            Detection improves with observation time. At 20 seconds, all 9 attack types are caught with {NEUROWALL_STATS.rocOptimal.fpr} false positive rate.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Duration</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Detected</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Evaded</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Notes</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {NEUROWALL_DURATION_SWEEP.map((row) => (
                <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/50">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] font-medium">{row.duration}</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-status-safe)]">{row.detected}</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">{row.evaded}</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{row.notes}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <!-- BrainFlow validation -->
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-4">Independent Validation</h3>
        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">
            Validated against BrainFlow's synthetic board ({NEUROWALL_STATS.brainflow.channels}-channel, 250Hz) as an independent EEG source not designed with the Neurowall detector. This confirms the coherence monitor generalizes beyond the built-in synthetic generator.
          </p>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-4 gap-4 text-center">
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-status-safe)]">{NEUROWALL_STATS.brainflow.detectionRate}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">Detection (5 attacks, 20 runs)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-status-safe)]">{NEUROWALL_STATS.brainflow.fpr}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">False Positive Rate</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">{NEUROWALL_STATS.brainflow.channels}ch</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">Channels Tested</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">{NEUROWALL_STATS.brainflow.csSpread}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">Cs Spread (< 0.15 PASS)</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Sovereignty Attacks -->
      <section id="sovereignty" class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-4">Sovereignty Attacks</h2>
        <div class="prose mb-8">
          <p>
            The most dangerous BCI attacks are the ones that slowly drift cognition without the subject's awareness. We call this class <strong>Sovereignty Attacks</strong> because they compromise the subject's sovereignty over their own neural state, violating <strong>Cognitive Liberty (CL)</strong> — the neurorights that protects the freedom to direct one's own thinking without external manipulation.
          </p>
          <p>
            The covert nature is what makes these categorically different: the subject cannot refuse what they cannot perceive.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Not new to BCIs -->
        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 mb-8" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-status-danger);">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-3">This Is Not New to BCIs</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">
            Subliminal steganography — hiding messages in signals the conscious mind cannot perceive — predates brain-computer interfaces entirely. The human critical flicker fusion (CFF) threshold is approximately 60 Hz. Displays refreshing above this rate can embed visual stimuli that the conscious mind cannot see but the visual cortex still processes and responds to. BCIs simply give the attacker a feedback loop: embed the stimulus, read the neural response, adapt.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
            <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Ming et al. (2023):</strong> Built a 60 Hz SSVEP BCI — above conscious perception — achieving 52.8 bits/min from stimuli users could not see.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Bian, Meng & Wu (2022):</strong> Trivial square wave injection forces any target BCI classification.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Zhang et al. (2021):</strong> Imperceptible adversarial perturbations force EEG-BCI spellers to output any character the attacker wants.</p>
            <p><strong class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">SAIL Lab (2023):</strong> Sensory-channel manipulation degrades motor imagery BCI performance across all subjects (p=0.0003). You don't hack the BCI — you attack the human.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Attack cards -->
        <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
          {NEUROWALL_SOVEREIGNTY_ATTACKS.map((attack) => (
            <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3 flex-wrap">
                <span class="text-sm font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">{attack.id}</span>
                <h3 class="text-base font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)]">{attack.name}</h3>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 ml-auto">
                  <span class={`text-xs font-semibold px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full ${attack.severity === 'High' ? 'bg-[var(--color-status-danger)]/10 text-[var(--color-status-danger)]' : 'bg-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]'}`}>
                    NISS {attack.niss}
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-xs font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
                    {attack.neurorights.join(' + ')}
                  </span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-3">{attack.description}</p>
              <div class="space-y-2">
                <div>
                  <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-status-danger)] mb-1">Detection Gap</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">{attack.detectionGap}</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-status-safe)] mb-1">Defense</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">{attack.defense}</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] mb-1">Historical Precedent</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">{attack.precedent}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <!-- Cognitive Liberty callout -->
        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent-tertiary);">
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Cognitive Liberty:</strong> All four sovereignty attacks primarily violate Cognitive Liberty (CL) — any technique scoring Cognitive Disruption at High/Critical AND Consent Violation at Explicit/Implicit triggers a CL violation flag in the <a href="/scoring/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] hover:underline">NISS scoring system</a>. Full technique database with 109 NISS-scored attacks available in the <a href="/TARA/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] hover:underline">TARA Atlas</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Policy Engine -->
      <section id="policy-engine" class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-6">Policy Engine (L3)</h2>
        <div class="prose mb-8">
          <p>
            The L3 policy agent uses a <code>RunematePolicy</code> engine that evaluates a prioritized rule stack against live signal state. Each rule specifies conditions (NISS threshold, anomaly score, sustained window count, detector type) and actions (epsilon override, stimulation suppression, alert level). A 4-window cooldown prevents rapid oscillation between rules.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium w-8">#</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Rule</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Condition</th>
                <th class="text-right py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Epsilon</th>
                <th class="text-right py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-faint)] font-medium">Alert</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {NEUROWALL_POLICY_RULES.map((rule) => (
                <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/50">
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">{rule.priority}</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] font-medium text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">{rule.name}</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">{rule.condition}</td>
                  <td class="py-3 px-4 text-right font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)]">{rule.epsilon}</td>
                  <td class={`py-3 px-4 text-right text-xs font-semibold uppercase ${rule.alert === 'critical' ? 'text-[var(--color-status-danger)]' : rule.alert === 'warning' ? 'text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]' : 'text-[var(--color-text-faint)]'}`}>
                    {rule.alert}
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 mt-6" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent-tertiary);">
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Policy-as-Code:</strong> Rules 1 and 4 also suppress outbound stimulation. Custom rule stacks can be provided programmatically or loaded from config. Future: compiled from <code>.staves</code> policy files via Runemate Forge, signed with ML-DSA, and hot-swapped on-chip without downtime.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TARA-Neurowall Vision -->
      <section id="tara-neurowall" class="mb-20">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-4">
          TARA-Neurowall <span class="text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] ml-2 align-middle">Future Vision</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="prose mb-8">
          <p>
            TARA is the threat intelligence. Neurowall is the active defense. TARA-Neurowall is the convergence: a Brain SIEM that combines threat knowledge with real-time neural security monitoring. The same architecture Kevin built at every company — identify signals, classify security events, deploy detections, tune for false positives — applied to the brain.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Planned Capabilities -->
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-8">
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-2 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">Score Ingestion</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Ingest anonymized Cs scores from QIF-compliant devices. Raw neural data never leaves the device — only protected scores with differential privacy applied locally.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-2 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">Fleet Monitoring</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Aggregate Cs trends across device populations to detect coordinated attacks, regional interference, or systematic device failures that single-device monitoring would miss.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-2 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">Threat Correlation</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Cross-reference live anomaly patterns against TARA's 109-technique taxonomy. Map detected events to specific attack signatures with NISS severity scores and neurorights impact.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-2 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">Federated Learning</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Improve detection models without centralizing data. Devices share encrypted gradients via secure aggregation — no individual neural patterns ever leave the device.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-2 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">User Dashboard</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Personal Cs history, anomaly alerts, and privacy controls. Users see their own data, choose what to share, and can opt out of any external transmission at any time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-2 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">Regulatory Reporting</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Generate compliance reports for FDA, IEEE, and institutional review boards. Automated evidence packages mapping detected events to neurorights violations and clinical impact.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

